Your companions will be as follows:<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Frodo - 7 strength, a decent companion. O Elbereth is KEY against Nazgul, try to save it for 9<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Merry - purely a pumper on wheels. He moves for Free with A Talent and pumps in a pinch. Great at 9.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Boromir - 13 strength, 15 against Nazgul. Calls up allies, wounds Orcs and Uruks, un overwhelmable. The most important companion, because he represents 6 extra companions.<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Aragorn - 14 strength, 16 against Nagul. Hatchetman. <br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Elrond - Troop killer, Cantea&#39;s daddy. Can be double Horned if nescessary to beat the biggies. <br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Heals Boromir in regroup to fight again. <br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
<br><br />
Have fun with this deck, I think it pretty tight, but if you see any glaring weaknesses put in the reviews. If you like it, lemme know too. Thanks for looking, and thanks for intelligent reviews. See ya at D-Con!<br />
